<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-695-981  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 695 981.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Dec 17 1990 v7 n50 p35(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CAT product converts hand-held scanners from Bandamp;W to color.andO;(Computer Aided Technology Inc.'s CAT Color Converter) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pompili, Tony.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Aided Technology Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Computer Aided Technology CAT Color Converter (Scanning device)(Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionScanning DevicesColorBundled Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Tony PompiliandM;Computer Aided Technology Inc. (CAT)plans next month to release a productthat offers buyers an inexpensive way to convert their monochrome hand-heldscanners to color scanners.andM;Called the CAT Color Converter, the package includes a combination ofscanning software and hardware, according to Gina Lee, vice president ofmarketing at CAT in Dallas.andM;The hardware component is a pad that contains three color filters.andP;  For eachprimary color, users place their scanner on the pad, calibrate the scanner tocorrespond with each filter and then scan the-image.andM;Software provided with the package converts the three scans into one red,green, blue PCX file that can be read by most popular paint programs, such asZSoft Corp.'s PC Paintbrush as well as the paint software provided by CAT inthe package.andM;The $149 CAT Color Converter works with hand-held scanners such as LogiTechInc.'s ScanMan and The Complete PC Inc.'s Hand Scan, according to Lee.andM;Computer Aided Technology can be reached at (214) 350-0888.andO;</TEXT></DOC>